usage: <Cooking_Instructions><Number_Of_Uses>250 Number of Servings per Pack 250</Number_Of_Uses><Recipes>Ultimate Cupcakes (Make 12)Ingredients150g softened butter 150g Silver Spoon Caster sugar 3 eggs at room temperature, beaten 1 tbsp Nielsen - Massey Pure Vanilla Extract Blend2 tbsp milk 150g Allinson Nature Friendly Self Raising FlourMethod1 Preheat over to 180c/Fan 160c/Gas Mark 4. Line a cup cake tin with cup cake cases.2. In a mixing bowl beat the butter and sugar until fluffy and pale. You can use a wooden spoon or an electric whisk.3. Beat the eggs together lightly with a fork, then add gradually to the butter and sugar mixture beating really well until the mixture is combined.4. Using a large metal spoon fold in the vanilla extract, milk and flour, lifting the mixture in a figure of eight to scoop up the flour and fold it in. Do this as lightly as you can to keep all the air in your mixture.5. Using dessert spoon, place a rounded spoonful in each cake case. Bake for about 15 minutes or until risen with a golden top. The cakes should feel firm and springy when touched in the centre6. Allow to cool for 5 minutes then remove from the tin and place on a wire rack, allowing them to cool completely.</Recipes></Cooking_Instructions>
